Physics is the most fundamental of the natural sciences — the study of matter, energy, space, and time, and the forces that govern their interactions. From Newton's laws of motion to Einstein's theory of relativity and the quantum mechanics of subatomic particles, physics has driven virtually every major technological revolution in human history. It seeks the deepest explanations of why the universe behaves as it does.
